The paper deals with monotonicity testing of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of isoperimetric results and random walks suggests information theory (cs.IT) as another possible sub-category. The study of hypergrids and augmented hypergrids involves geometric and combinatorial aspects, which could fall under computational geometry (cs.CG) and structural information and communication complexity (cs.SI).
